headline: Why Carnival (CCL) Stock Is Trading Lower Today
summary: Shares of cruise ship company Carnival (NYSE:CCL) fell 2.7% in the afternoon session after the major indices continued to retreat (Nasdaq -1.5%, S&P 500 -1.2%) amid profit-taking and renewed concerns about tariffs.
